  <brief_title>Seroquel Switching Study: Feasibility of Switching Any Antipsychotic Treatment to Seroquel in Patients With Schizophrenia</brief_title>
  <official_title>A 12-week International, Multicenter, Open Label, Non-comparative Study to Evaluate the Feasibility of Switching Any Antipsychotic Treatment to Sustained-release Quetiapine Fumarate (SEROQUELÂ®) in Patients With Schizophrenia</official_title>
  <sponsors>
    <lead_sponsor>
      <agency>AstraZeneca</agency>
      <agency_class>Industry</agency_class>
    </lead_sponsor>
  </sponsors>
  <source>AstraZeneca</source>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to document the clinical benefit of quetiapine (Seroquel)
      sustained release (SR) after switching from another ongoing antipsychotic treatment,
      regardless of the reason for the switch.

      PLEASE NOTE: Seroquel SR and Seroquel XR refer to the same formulation. The SR designation
      was changed to XR after consultation with FDA.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
